Mahasiddhas" (Inner Traditions International, One Park St., Rochester, VT., 
05767: $24.95; 208 pp.), translated from the Tibetan by Keith Dowman, 
illustrated by Robert Beer. The mahasiddhas are the great saints of the 
Vajrayana (Tantra) tradition of Buddhism, one of whose distinguishing tenets is 
that enlightenment may be found in the unlikeliest circumstances. 
</P>
